#MeToo is a movement, not a moment. In just 2 years, 15 states have passed laws to ban mandatory NDAs and forced arbitration, extend statutes of limitations, & expand protections to more workers. State legislatures have intro'd 200+ bills. Let's keep the momentum going!

Since #MeToo, @HouseDemocrats have taken bold action to reauthorize #VAWA, ban mandatory arbitration, eliminate the tipped minimum wage and overhaul harassment rules in Congress. We're not done yet. We won't back down until all are safe from sexual violence & free to thrive!

Two years ago #MeToo changed us. It's become part of our national consciousness, demanding better for survivors & future generations. We can't let the words ring hollow. We must press forward for lasting change - a culture that believes & laws that respect survivors.
